
//STEP 1 : CREATE POLICY
PUT _plugins/_ism/policies/wazuh-alerts-retention
{
  "policy": {
    "description": "Delete wazuh-alerts indices after 2 days",
    "default_state": "hot",
    "states": [
      {
        "name": "hot",
        "actions": [],
        "transitions": [
          {
            "state_name": "delete",
            "conditions": { "min_index_age": "2d" }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "name": "delete",
        "actions": [{ "delete": {} }],
        "transitions": []
      }
    ]
  }
}

//STEP 2 : ATTACH TO INDICES


//policy with comments
PUT _plugins/_ism/policies/wazuh-alerts-retention
{
  "policy": {
    "description": "Delete wazuh-alerts indices after 2 days",
    // Human-readable note about what this policy does

    "default_state": "hot",
    // Every new index starts in the "hot" state (normal, actively used)

    "states": [
      {
        "name": "hot",
        // The starting state - no special actions happen here,
        // it just waits and checks the transition condition below

        "actions": [],
        // No actions performed while in "hot" state

        "transitions": [
          {
            "state_name": "delete",
            // Where to move the index once the condition is met

            "conditions": { "min_index_age": "2d" }
            // The condition: once an index is 3 days old
            // (based on its creation date, e.g. wazuh-alerts-4.x-2026.07.20
            // created on 07.20 turns 3 days old on 07.23), move it to
            // the "delete" state
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "name": "delete",
        // The final state - this is where deletion actually happens

        "actions": [{ "delete": {} }],
        // The actual delete action - removes the index permanently

        "transitions": []
        // No further transitions - this is the end of the lifecycle
      }
    ]
  }
}

//Wazuh Dashboard → Index Management → State Management Policies (or via Dev Tools

//content are stored on the indexer so you cant necessarity check on the device as is 
GET _plugins/_ism/policies/wazuh-alerts-retention

//cheatsheat
## Check existing policies

- **List all ISM policies:**
  ```
  GET _plugins/_ism/policies
  ```

- **Check a specific policy by name:**
  ```
  GET _plugins/_ism/policies/wazuh-alerts-retention
  ```

- **Check which indices have a policy attached, and their current state:**
  ```
  GET _plugins/_ism/explain/wazuh-alerts-4.x-*
  ```

## Create / update a policy

- **Create or overwrite a policy (same name = update):**
  ```
  PUT _plugins/_ism/policies/wazuh-alerts-retention
  { ...policy JSON body... }
  ```

- **Attach a policy to matching indices:**
  ```
  POST _plugins/_ism/add/wazuh-alerts-4.x-*
  { "policy_id": "wazuh-alerts-retention" }
  ```

## Remove a policy

- **Detach the policy from indices first (recommended before deleting):**
  ```
  POST _plugins/_ism/remove/wazuh-alerts-4.x-*
  ```

- **Delete the policy definition itself:**
  ```
  DELETE _plugins/_ism/policies/wazuh-alerts-retention
  ```

- **Confirm it's gone:**
  ```
  GET _plugins/_ism/policies
  ```

## Manual index deletion (no policy involved, immediate)

- **View all current indices:**
  ```
  GET _cat/indices/wazuh-alerts-*?v
  ```

- **Delete a specific day's index:**
  ```
  DELETE wazuh-alerts-4.x-2026.07.20
  ```

- **Delete a range using a wildcard:**
  ```
  DELETE wazuh-alerts-4.x-2026.06.*
  ```